outputs.output_descr:
1. Enhancing the resilience of coastal communities and protective ecosystems through community-led adaptation interventions, focusing on coastal afforestation and livelihood diversification; 
2. Enhancing national, sub-national, and local capacities of government authorities and sectoral planners to understand climate risk dynamics in coastal areas and implement appropriate risk reduction measures; 
3. Reviewing and revising coastal management practices and policies with a view on increasing community resilience to climate change impacts in coastal areas; and 
4. Developing a functional system for the collection, distribution and internalization of climate-related knowledge.
